THE PLAN ACCOMPLISHED ITS PURPOSE OF PROVIDING SUPPLEMENTAL UNEMPLOYMENT AND SICK BENEFITS TO ELIGIBLE PARTICIPANTS THAT ARE MEMBERS OF THE PLUMBERS, PIPE FITTERS AND MECHANICAL EQUIPMENT SERVICE LOCAL UNION NO 392.
THE PLAN HAS MEMBERS THAT MAY ELECT ONE OR MORE MEMBERS OF THE GOVERNING BOARD
PRIOR TO ELECTRONICALLY SUBMITTING THE RETURN, A REVEIW OF FORM 990 WAS CONDUCTED BY MICHAEL T. HAYES, CPA (PREPARER OF RETURN) WITH THE TRUSTEES AND PLAN ADMINISTRATOR.
THE ADMINISTRATOR AND UNION TRUSTEES ARE PAID THROUGH THE HEALTH AND WELFARE FUND (E.I. NO 31-0561070), AND THE HEALTH AND WELFARE FUND IS REIMBURSED BY THE SUPPLEMENTAL UNEMPLOYMENT BENEFIT FUND.
OFFICE STAFF IS PAID THROUGH THE HEALTH AND WELFARE FUND (E.I. NO 31- 0561070) AND THE HEALTH AND WELFARE FUND IS REIMBURSED BY THE SUPPLEMENTAL UNEMPLOYMENT BENEFIT FUND.
THE ORGANIZATION DOES NOT MAKE ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE.
